This paper deals with the problem of point cloud segmentation for road object detection using LiDAR data. The paper proposes a new model structure and unsupervised domain adaptation techniques to improve the accuracy of the segmentation. The paper also discusses the use of simulators to generate synthetic data for training, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning techniques for segmentation and domain adaptation also falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
